metadata.name: Harmony in chaos #33
metadata.description:
The human spirit is an enigmatic one-of-a-kind. It has always been a conundrum for people who want to understand the depth of it, but no one has ever made it through. Once generated, the spirit is like a blank canvas; everyone has a slightly different spirit hue. As time goes, our spirits grow more influenced by our daily activities, emotions, and feelings... We intend to view the front of the surface of it, as we do with everything, but there are numerous scratches, scars, and traces beneath the surface.

---
Created using vanilla javascript
KrouniHatim - Nov22
---

metadata.name: Action Fields #178
metadata.description:
A generative painting based on abstract expressionism and the action paintings of Jackson Pollock.

Several different flow fields are used to create paths which are then painted in one of four different styles (pastel, paint, Pollock, black+gold). Additional features affect the background, path length + angles, level of detail, and mess (drips and splats). 

NOTES: 
- Some variations of the Pollock style may appear slightly different between browsers, but will render consistently in the same browser. 
- On slower devices, it may take some time to being drawing due to the background rendering.
- If you get a browser warning that the page is taking a long time, press continue.

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 1200x928px
Press ’p’ to pause/resume.

Add '&size=#' to the end of the live view URL to render a variation of your edition at a resolution from 300 to 5,000 px. The ideal higher resolution is 2,000px.

metadata.name: Splinter #15
metadata.description:
This release marks my first anniversary on the fx(hash) platform! I want to extend a huge thank you to everyone for a fantastic year, and I'm looking forward to many more in the generative-art world!

The basic algorithm is an evolution of the one I used in my first release, Raked Strokes. Instead of mimicking a brush with parallel segments, I'm using perpendicular line segments to define the overall abstract shape and then drawing each line in a simulated media. This approach blends my first attempts at natural media with everything I've learned in the past year.

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press 's' to save a screenshot. The image size is 2357x3000px
Press 'p' to pause/resume during drawing.

Features
- Base path shape: line, circle, diamond, or rectangle
- Elements defining the spacing and orientation of the line segments
- The base path painted in the background
- Monochrome, dark background, and selection of palettes
- Ink pen styling: thickness, quality, and background blocking
- Paint styling: color distribution, quality
- Shapes: triangle, polygons, criteria for insertion
- Shapes overdrawing: outlines or perpendicular segments

metadata.name: Reading a book #277
metadata.description:
The formal structure of a book is beautiful by itself, but its aesthetic is the tacit atmosphere within which events take place in a story.

The WebGL real-time animation sets up an initial grid based on the fxhash. The grid cells get subdivided into another grid and the resulting cells become filled with pixels in color (~33%) or black and white (~66%).
The colored pixels come in 3 different coloring styles.
- Big Palette (~49%)
- Small Palette (~49%)
- Monochrome [b/w] (~2%)
4 noise algorithms modify the pixels of selected grid cells while at the same time 4 reset algorithms reassemble the initial image. The selected cells switch over time.

metadata.name: Parrot #52
metadata.description:
Generative art, written with Vanilla JS & 6 layers of png is used (Tree branch, Toes, Parrot body, Beak, Nose jewel, eye glass, Gold Pendant , scarf, Tie, Cap, VR Head set). 
- Pixel based Image processing 
- Color inversion is achieved by subtracting each RGB color value from 255
- Algorithm reads each 6 layers of the parrot in memory and apply Color inversion
In the objective of decorating the squeaky birdy for all seasons I started layering with various traits and accessories. While the computed combinations surprised me with a trans-seasonal wardrobe for the birdy which are unique.
Few mix-matches like Nose jewel, Eye glass, Cap, VR glass remains cute.

metadata.name: Imperium #494
metadata.description:
Imperium is a study of shapes and colors, and how a very small set of shapes and colors, when given equally simple rules, can create a great variety of patterns that may bring meaning to the viewer.

Press the s key for a quick download at the current resolution, and press the space bar to display the export and information menu.

For more information, read the collection guide:
https://medium.com/@MrMallory/imperium-the-collection-guide-cd9ab7e05aa0
